		<profileDesc>
			<abstract>
				<p>To understand the brain mechanisms involved in reward prediction on different time scales, we developed a Markov decision task that requires prediction of both immediate and future rewards, and analyzed subjects&apos; brain activities using functional MRI. We estimated the time course of reward prediction and reward prediction error on different time scales from subjects&apos; performance data, and used them as the explanatory variables for SPM analysis. We found topog-raphic maps of different time scales in medial frontal cortex and striatum. The result suggests that different cortico-basal ganglia loops are specialized for reward prediction on different time scales.</p>
			</abstract>
